  "text": "The second group consisted of strains that were collected from February 2006 to September 2007 from patients at the Hematology Clinic of the Public Hospital No. 1 in Gdaesk. We included 95 isolates of C. albicans from 76 patients ( Table 1) . The strains were isolated from stool (37), sputum (30), throat [CITATION_1] , blood (7) and oral cavity [CITATION_2] . Thirty eight of those C. albicans strains, isolated from different clinical specimens (sputum, stool, oral cavity or blood) from nineteen patients (two strains each), were used to study genotype variations in a patient.",
